messages.message:
@Loc if someone wants to write a quick method which does a diff of “pip freeze” and the requirements.txt — you detect whether you are up-to-date or not.

You can put that command in “build-python.mk (http://build-python.mk)”

Let’s not put it on the path of “make” right now until we’ve tested it out, but you could totally do that diff and wrap it in a make command
